  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance for Populations Affected by Border Crises (Lake Chad Basin and Liptako Gourma) in Niger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM as co-lead of the Shelters and Non-Food Items Working Group, which is chaired by the Ministry of Humanitarian Action and Disaster Management (MAH / GC), is providing emergency humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable populations affected by conflicts and / or victims of floods in order to relieve and reinforce their adaptive capacities and avoid the state of current insecurity in which they live. These are the internally displaced persons, refugees and the most vulnerable host families in the host areas / villages. Households are being assisted with emergency shelters and non-food items.</narrative>
  </description>
